Of the 380 plus usages of penuma in the Greek New Testament, the
editors of the King James Version deliberately misinterpreted about
180 of the verses by adding to, taking away from, or changing the word
of God.  They did this by adding the definite article to the English
before spirit when it was not in the Greek texct, by omitting the
definite article from the English when it was in the Greek text, by
changing the noun hagion to a proper adjective, by changing the
adjective hagion to a proper adjective, and by changing the noun
pneuma to a proper noun.  They rendered &quot;pneuma hagion&quot; as &quot;the Holy
